PersInt is a class which as the same suggests, you can use to create persistent Integers. 

Methods -

PersInt(string fileName) 

	Constructor. You'll have to provide a name to construct PersInt. You must use this name the next time you refer to the integers you have created using the object created.
	

void addInt(string key, int value)

	Used to add a new persistent integer. Should provide a key(which you must use to refer to that integer from now on) and the value of the integer.
	
int getInt(string key)

	Used to get the value of a particular stored integer. Returns -9999 if no key was found.

